### OVERVIEW

#### About the TA-hdhomerun

| Author | B. Daniel Potter |
| --- | --- |
| App Version | 1.0 (beta) |
| Vendor Products | HDHomerun Connect |
| Has index-time operations | false |
| Create an index | false |
| Implements summarization | false |

The TA-hdhomerun allows a Splunk® Enterprise administrator to easily extract and parse fields from the HDHomerun Connect log.html

#### Release notes
In order to collect the data you need to extract it from your local HDHomerun Connect in some way. I have done this with a bash script that leverages curl and some basic parsing and scripting to add only new log lines to the log.  My script is not that efficient, but reading the file to a new log over and over causes splunk to reingest the events multiple times leading to bad data.

I would like to solicit assistance in creating a better way to get this data. For now this should provide a good starting point for HDHomerun devices that would like to splunk it's activity.

You will find the latest version of my data collection script on splunkbase in the TA-HDHomerun add-on description.

##### About this release

Version 1.0.0 of the TA-homerun is Compatible with:

| Splunk Enterprise versions | 6.x, 7.x |
| --- | --- |
| CIM | --- |
| Platforms | Platform independent |
| Vendor Products | HDHomerun Connect|
| Lookup file changes | none |

#### Splunk Enterprise system requirements

Because this add-on runs on Splunk Enterprise, all of the [Splunk Enterprise system requirements](http://docs.splunk.com/Documentation/Splunk/latest/Installation/Systemrequirements) apply.

#### Configure TA-hdhomerun

You may need to adjust the eventtype=hdhomerun to include your correct data directory. Otherwise this TA is plug and play. Deploy to Indexers and Search Head(s), or if your data is sent to a Heavy Forwarder, install to HF and Search Head(s)

## USER GUIDE

### Data types

This app provides the index-time and search-time knowledge for the following types of data from Trend Micro Control Manager (CEF):

hdhomerun

